## Component Based Architecture

What is a "component"?
  Components are independent and reusable bits of code.

What are the characteristics of a component?
  Path. Name. Type. Version Number. Platform. 
  Organization. Interaction. Interdependence. Integration.

What are the advantages of using component based architecture?
  There are many benefits. Reduced development and testing time, enhanced reliability and flexibility to change applications by adding or replacing components.
  


## What is Props and How to Use it in React

What is "props" short for?
  Properties.

How are props used in React?
  They can be used to store data that can be accessed by the children of a React component.

What is the flow of props?
To pass data from one component to another component.


